    <h2>What's Included in Our Dryer Vent Installation</h2>

    <ul>
      <li><strong>Site assessment</strong> — we measure the optimal vent path and identify any code compliance issues before starting</li>
      <li><strong>Rigid metal ductwork only</strong> — we install UL-listed rigid aluminum or galvanized steel duct (4" diameter). We never use plastic or foil flex duct, which violates California fire codes</li>
      <li><strong>Wall penetration if needed</strong> — we core drill through drywall, stucco, or brick and install a proper exterior vent cap with backdraft damper</li>
      <li><strong>Foil tape sealing</strong> — all joints sealed with foil tape (not duct tape), the industry standard for heat resistance up to 400°F</li>
      <li><strong>Post-installation airflow test</strong> — we verify proper airflow before we leave</li>
      <li><strong>Code-compliant routing</strong> — maximum 35-foot vent length, 4 elbows maximum per California building code</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>When Do You Need Dryer Vent Installation?</h2>

    <h3>New Dryer in a Different Location</h3>
    <p>Moving your laundry setup — to a new room, a garage, or a condo's interior closet — requires a new vent path. Interior laundry rooms in LA condos often need vents routed through ceilings or floors, which requires licensed work and city code compliance.</p>

    <h3>Replacing Plastic or Foil Flex Duct</h3>
    <p>Many older LA homes were installed with plastic or flexible foil ducts — both of which are now prohibited under California building code due to fire risk. If your dryer takes longer than usual to dry clothes, or you see a d80/d90 error, a crushed or clogged flex duct is often the cause. We replace it with rigid metal duct.</p>

    <h3>Vent Damaged or Disconnected</h3>
    <p>Pest damage, renovation work, or simple age can disconnect or crush the ductwork inside the wall. We've found completely disconnected vents in LA homes that were venting hot moist air directly into the wall cavity — a mold risk.</p>

    <h3>New Construction or Remodel</h3>
    <p>If you're adding a laundry room to your home or garage, we install the complete vent system from scratch and ensure it passes city inspection.</p>

    <h2>Dryer Vent Installation Across LA, Orange County &amp; Ventura County</h2>

    <p>We serve all of Los Angeles County — including West Hollywood, Burbank, Glendale, Pasadena, Santa Monica, Long Beach, Culver City, and Koreatown. In Orange County we cover Irvine, Anaheim, Huntington Beach, Costa Mesa, Newport Beach, and Fullerton. In Ventura County we serve Thousand Oaks, Simi Valley, Oxnard, and Camarillo.</p>

    <p>Same-day appointments available Monday–Saturday 8am–8pm. Call <strong>(323) 990-7550</strong> or book online. CSLB Licensed #1138898 · BBB A+ · 4.9★ rated.</p>

